history.content: After you try to enroll in the conflicting class (and get the error message), a notification should appear in the Notifications section of your CalCentral home page with a form to fill out.

children.subject:
Yes, if you waitlist for a conflicting course, you'll never be able to get off the waitlist.

For EECS courses (and EECS courses only), you should see @2571.

history.content: While the student's answer is probably correct that the calcentral form will appear, it is often useless -- especially for courses with waitlists.  You should feel free to search for previous posts in EECS 101 Piazza where staff have spent a good amount of time explaining the cs and ee departmental supplementary processes for conflict forms.
